## âš™ï¸ Setup Instructions

1ï¸âƒ£ **Clone the repository**:

git clone https://github.com/lakshayparashar28/cyber_agent.git
cd cyber_agent

2ï¸âƒ£ Create and activate virtual environment:
python -m venv env
.\env\Scripts\activate      # On Windows
source env/bin/activate     # On Mac/Linux

3ï¸âƒ£ Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

4ï¸âƒ£ Set up your Telegram Bot:

Create a bot via @BotFather.

Get the bot token and your Telegram chat ID.

Save them in a bot_credentials.txt file (first line: token, second line: chat ID).

ğŸš€ Running the Project
1ï¸âƒ£ Run the Front-End App
Launch the app to use drag-and-drop CSV upload and manual login entry:

streamlit run login_interface.py

Use the batch upload for bulk file scanning.
Use manual entry to check new logins live.
Explanations will display immediately, using your LLaMA explainer.

ğŸ§  How It Works
âœ… Model Training: Trained an Isolation Forest on historical login data for anomaly detection.
âœ… Prediction: Flags new logins as suspicious if outliers.
âœ… Explanation: Uses LLaMA (or your local LLM) to generate readable, explainable reasons for suspicion.
âœ… Alerting: Sends a Telegram message instantly if a suspicious login is detected.
âœ… Logging: Stores all login attempts and flagged suspicious attempts for audit and review.

